onmental philosophers and demonstrating the relevance of his thought for our current ethical and environmental problems. Crafting strong supporting arguments for Jonas's insightful view of ethics as a matter of both reason and emotion, Morris convincingly lays out his account of the basis of our responsibilities not only to the biosphere but also to current and future generations of beings.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aEnvironmental ethics. 0aEnvironmental responsibility. 0aOntology. 0aResponsibility. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Ethics. 4aPhilosophy : Phenomenology. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy and Biology. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438448824423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438448824/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles